<div class='talk-article talk-article--main' id='talk' itemscope itemtype='http://schema.org/VideoObject'>
<link href='http://www.ted.com/talks/paul_zak_trust_morality_and_oxytocin' itemprop='url'>
<meta content='Trust, morality — and oxytocin?' itemprop='name'>
<meta content='What drives our desire to behave morally? Neuroeconomist Paul Zak shows why he believes oxytocin (he calls it "the moral molecule") is responsible for trust, empathy and other feelings that help build a stable society.' itemprop='description'>
<meta content='PT16M34S' itemprop='duration'>
<link content='https://tedcdnpi-a.akamaihd.net/r/tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/cbeba08e876754c0fb906a52351d45cfed6624c5_800x600.jpg?quality=95&amp;w=480' itemprop='thumbnailUrl'>
<span itemprop='author' itemscope itemtype='http://schema.org/Person'>
<link href='/speakers/paul_zak' itemprop='url'>
<meta content='Paul Zak' itemprop='name'>
<link href='http://tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/cdb9f15bf2a99648b5ccddf55da4d98acabd3919_254x191.jpg' itemprop='image'>
