<div class='talk-subsection'>
<div class='talk-top__details'>
<p class='talk-description' lang='en'>
What drives our desire to behave morally? Neuroeconomist Paul Zak shows why he believes oxytocin (he calls it "the moral molecule") is responsible for trust, empathy and other feelings that help build a stable society.
</p>
<div class='talk-more'>
<ul class='sl'>
<li class='l3 talk-more__item'>
<a class='talk-more__link' href='/talks/paul_zak_trust_morality_and_oxytocin/transcript?language=en' id='open-transcript'><i class="icon icon_transcript talk-more__icon talk-more__icon__transcript" title="Interactive transcript"></i><span class="screen-reader-text">Interactive transcript</span><span class='talk-more__label'>Interactive transcript</span></a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class='talk-speakers'>
<div class='talk-speaker media'>
<a class='talk-speaker__image media__image media__image--thumb' href='/speakers/paul_zak'>
<span class="thumb thumb--square"><span class="thumb__sizer"><span class="thumb__tugger"><img alt="" class=" thumb__image" play="false" src="https://tedcdnpi-a.akamaihd.net/r/tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/cdb9f15bf2a99648b5ccddf55da4d98acabd3919_254x191.jpg?" /><span class="thumb__aligner"></span></span></span></span>
</a>
<div class='talk-speaker__details media__message'>
<div class='talk-speaker__name h10'>
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/paul_zak">Paul Zak</a>
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__description'>
Neuroeconomist
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__bio'>
A pioneer in the field of neuroeconomics, Paul Zak is uncovering how the hormone oxytocin promotes trust, and proving that love is good for business.
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/paul_zak">Full bio</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
